Mezmo (50th Sorcerer - Palomides. 41 Body, 34 Mind) - The Sorcerer is a versatile class that can be very powerful under predictable, "ideal" circumstances, thus we solo very very well in PvE.  However, because of our low defensive capabilites, lack of bolt range, and the difficulty of maintaining a charmed pet, RvR is a nightmare for most Sorcerers.  Playing against real human players throws a wrench in our "ideal" circumstances and makes the class ridiculously weak.  Spells like confuse & amnesia are essentially useless in RvR.  It takes too long to get (and keep) a useful pet in RvR, thus we usually go without.  Our nukes are too weak to rely on for damage without a good pet, especially with body damage(high resists).  Mez is the only real reason for us to spec our Mind Line, but the power of mez has been diminished to the point that there is no longer ANY reason to spec Mind.  We have been placed in the role of Primary CC for our realm, yet we lack the other useful skills of the Bard (Speed & Healing) & Healer (Healing & Buffing), and we lack the HPs & Armor of these classes as well.  We can't do our job if we are dead, and we are dead too often.  The main problem in regards to CC is that we have no Insta-Cast compared to the primary CC's of other realms.  The first mez of a battle is often very important & we will never win with a 3sec cast compared to the insta-cast of a Bard or Healer.<P>--------------------<P><B>Quote 7/2/02 - i3ullseye, Sorcerer Team Lead: Actually no, i am not 'your' representative. this has been stated before. many TLs do not post ANYWHERE except the pendragn boards. Noone has to try to get ANY feedback from the general populace.</B><P><B>**********************</B><P>Palomides / Alat-Seldi<BR>Mezmo - Level 50.1 Sorcerer<BR>Tagalong - Level 43 Enhance Cleric<BR>Siege - Level 33 Armsman<BR>Terrenus - Level 28 Earth Wizard<BR>Miracle - Level 11 Rejuv Cleric<BR>Recurve - Level 10 Scout
