Okay, i3ullseye, I had promised myself I wouldn't expend anymore energy trying to lobby for this class....<P>But never say never, right...<P>Jenlei(Myrcil Mindreaver (41.5 R2L6))<BR>1. Ranged insta-cast mez is rediculous. If it must stay, then it must be point blank. PERIOD.<P>2. Charming a monster shouldn't artificially weaken it.  Why give us the ability to charm even cons if they never end up even cons anyway?<P>3. Spec line DoT should be AE with Range scaling similarly to the way AE mez currently does.  Current stacking properties should remain.<P>4. AE Mez range should be standardized to 350 radius.  Making us the only primary CC class that has to spec high to even get that radius was poor judgement.  The duration can scale up with spec, but radius should be standard at least up to the level 34 AE. <P>5. In a wierd twist of evolutionary fate, I now find myself in the position of asking for the mind line to be looked at.  Matter is almost viable, but with all the changes to CC and mez resists, Mind is hurting.<P>6. And finally, in the name of all that is holy, have someone with programming talent and a set of balls to match revisit the interruption code and change it so that the absurdity of trying to equalize the chance for interrupts between fast and slow swinging weapons is replaced with something a little more realistic.  I mean honestly, if you were to fight two different people, one with a huge mutha of an axe that he could swing at you every 5 seconds and one with a small dagger that could poke you 3 times a second.  Who the hell do you think would interrupt your concentration more? This *tick tick tick* crap is *sick sick sick*.  You trade interrupt potential for higher slower swinging damage.  Its common sense.  <P><BR>Sorry i3ullseye, longer than three lines....guess I had some frustration hidden away.  Just pick the important parts.<P>--------------------<P>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<BR>Myrcil the Briton Matter/Mind Sorcerer<BR>Member of the Furious Pantaloons<BR>Galahad Server<BR>Member of the Sorcerer Testing Team in Beta<BR>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<P>"Who could ever calculate the path of a molecule?<BR>How do we know that the creations of worlds are not determined by falling grains of sand?"<BR>  --Victor Hugo, Les Miserables
