Sigma Stellaris, 50 Sorcerer, Percival, Retired<P>The Sorcerer is the greatest trickster the game has ever known.  We look great on paper, offering a wide variety of abilities; in practice, every single ability is turned on end, and it's the little things that make us "possibly able" to do so many things, but never able to be good at any one of them.  Our Job title as Primary Crowd Control for Albion only brings us grief, as we are embaressed to say that we cannot do our job adaquately, not in PvE and most *certainly* not in RvR.  The core issues, quite simply put...Survivability and Competative CC Capabilities.
