<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
The Sorcerer class has a number of problems.  It has been deemed as a support class/main CC class because of pets/roots/aoe mez/debuffs which is all good; sorcerers are one of the better classes suited for PvE, but when it comes to RvR we are crippled.  I think that our lack of effectiveness in RvR is mainly because other classes we are up against can do what we can do, but much better.<P>   Our CC simply does not work in RvR.  Any time we are seen getting a mez off, we are killed almost immediately, and then target by the insta-mezzers continually from them.  We have no defense to these insta-mezzes and anyone will tell you they are far more powerful than a castable mez when it comes to battle.  Aoe root is a nice spell, however it is mez that is winning battles.  The Druid casts an instant-aoe root.  Our lack of instant CC spells makes it very difficult to CC in RvR, and once we are known to be a CC, it becomes nearly impossible.<P>   This is well known by Sorcerers that have participated a lot in high-end RvR; as a result many have respec to body-nukers or DoTers.  In both cases we are already weakened.  Body dmg is poor due to resists, and matter spec DoTs do not compare to that of a Cabby. A very popular template is the 48body/24mind; for the nukes and some mezzing.  Now take a look at a fully specced light Eld: specced cold nukes, nearsight, 350radius aoe mez.... in essence those people have become poor nuking(due to body resists), weak mezzing Elds, without nearsight or stun.<BR>  <BR>   The Telekenisis line I am particuarly disappointed with.  The new spells added here were, in my opinon, carelessly.  The aoe and single target debuff debuff the same amount of dex/quick.  We already have a dex/quick debuff in our body line.  Debuffs have yet to be noticably effective.   Our snare being the only one at a 1350 range was rather insulting; we are in now way endangering to the power of other classes.<P>Like I said before, sorc are pretty good when it comes to PvE.  But when it comes to RvR we are forced to adapt roles very different from that which we trained.   This will be even more frustrating to sorcs that cannot respec.  What sorcerers need is either instants to make our CC reliable, effective debuffs, (resist debuffs were great when they were instants.....we were one of the few classes that were not overpowered by having them..) or some truely original additions to our spec lines.  As it stands, we do not accomplish anything in RvR as far as support goes, and when we adopt roles for dealing dmg, we fall short of all the other casting clases.<P>     Suggestions:<BR>-Long range (2000-2300) single target mez<BR>-An instant-anything; mez/root/stun(magi have all those damn stuns...)/DoT/life-tap/amnesia<BR>-Charm higher lvls<BR>-Better pet control; chose what spells you want your pet to cast<BR>-Easier ways to get pets:  buy pets? summon an emergency pet?<BR>-350 radius on all aoe mez/root<BR>-Instant aoe mez-dispel<BR>-GTAoe something...DoT?  <P>     New, original spells suggestions:<BR>-Illusionary pets: tangeable decoys that look like players but cannot do dmg or take dmg<BR>-GTAoe stealther finder<BR>-Mind abilities? danger sense for stealthers/ sensing enemies that are on other side of a wall<BR>-A confuse that will actually  make a player hit his allies a few times (on a timer)<BR>-melee interupter- like amensia, but interupts styled attacks<BR>-GTAoe Do<P>Xelacia- lvl 49 Sorc from Gawaine
</FONT>
